parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and shutting down can cause loss of power steering, acceleration, and control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts down while driving
often without warning; the low oil pressure warning light may come on; the vehicle may experience a loss of power steering and acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can cause the engine to shut down, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded; it can also lead to premature engine wear and damage.
symptoms: The vehicle burns through oil quickly
often requiring frequent oil changes; the oil level may drop rapidly
causing the engine to shut down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the stop/start system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's stop/start system fails to restart the engine after shutting down; the vehicle may stall or shut down while driving.
